Alice Walker // "Some periods of our growth are so confusing that we don’t even recognize that growth is happening. We may feel hostile or angry or weepy and hysterical, or we may feel depressed. It would never occur to us, unless we stumbled on a book or a person who explained to us, that we were in fact in the process of change... Whenever we grow, we tend to feel it, as a young seed must feel the weight and inertia of the earth as it seeks to break out of its shell on its way to becoming a plant... Often the feeling is anything but pleasant. But what is most unpleasant is the not knowing what is happening... Those long periods when something inside ourselves seems to be waiting, holding its breath, unsure about what the next step should be, eventually become the periods we wait for, for it is in those periods that we realize we are being prepared for the next phase of our life and that, in all probability, a new level of personality is about to be revealed."
Alice Walker

Good morning. Blue mountains 🇯🇲🙏🏽

Nanny falls. Healing waters.  Queen Nanny Of the Maroons.  Maroon town. Moore town. Late 17th century A settlement of self emancipated Africans/Jamaicans in the blue mountains of Jamaica. Queen Nanny led with clear military prowess and rumored spiritual powers. Attacked a few plantations to free her people and diligently protected her community. The terrain is tough, they used it in their favor. This water fall was used by soldiers to revitalize and recalibrate after battles with the British. Crystal clear and ice cold. Re-member. Put the pieces back together. I was fortunate to have the falls to myself. How? idk. Nanny of the Maroons, look her up, powerful. Nanny of the Maroons. Nanny of the Maroons.  To think I’m bathing in the same place…

Over the years I’ve received so much love and inspiration from fans, from the audience, from YOU. I don’t say it enough. 
  THANK YOU.  Sincerely.  THANK YOU🧸

What about evolution?
Change is unavoidable 
some would say decay
But what of evolution?
I’ve always been fascinated by evolution. 
A thumb. Wings. Survival. The brain.
A species.
Ours.
Evolving into or towards…well… 
What?
We have seamlessly merged with machine. 2 decades it took?
Tiny computers On or near our person 24/7 ,less for the lucky few who sleep.
In my Dreams of who we are becoming or could become. I’ve always imagined mountaintop lotus position, ascension, harmony. Each era we become better. More sanitary. More humane. Now I realize how stuck in the past I was/am. Our processing speed, access, the answer is available to us…via the machine. But what toward?
Galavanting through smoky summers
Heat like we’ve never known 
Alert after alert After alert
But it’s not yet unbearable, soooooo
With so much at stake
I personally do the same things
Point out the flaw with no solution
Driving, flying, blasting the aircon to see the world.
To vacate. 
The desire may become a necessity. Less luxurious then. To avoid said burning and flooding and the like.
I’ve grown comfortable with my upper middle class actress life. Style. Real cozy. Not flashy but I’m surrounded by nice things all the time. Identity anchoring on it even. Maybe. Nice things. God and man made.
Though one can be renewed, the other?  WE SHALL SEE.
Real cozy, real comfortable. taking pictures like we the “ haves”. While the real “haves” the “ haves for true”, “ love n know money long time, Haves”. While they prepare. Quietly. Sans instagram post. 
Acquiring what came from stars. Real stars. Sky type.
WE SHALL SEE.
The little things I do feel silly in the grand scheme. Recycle. Turn off the light. The solar panels. The ethical business. The local farm. But it helps, right? It must. Else, what are we evolving towards?  @eric.saulz 📸

There’s something in that South Carolina water… How a whole New Yorker like me got caught in this southern circle I will never know.  I’m very thankful.  I’m just a saucer catching the overflow… I am surrounded by love. Shoutout to LOVE.  Shoutout to joy bringers, truth tellers, style slayers, word  providers, and the ones who are not afraid of working the kinks and cries out.  Shoutout to tomorrow… shoutout to friendship and how it grows.  Shoutout to journeys, and stick-to-it-ness… shoutout to chocolate, flowers, crisp photos, sisterhood and platform shoes.  Shoutout to toolkits provided by God.  Again, shoutout to LOVE.

You have no idea how hard I've looked for a gift to bring You. Nothing seemed right.  What's the point of bringing gold to the gold mine, or water to the ocean.  Everything I came up with was like taking spices to the Orient. It's no good giving my heart and my soul because you already have these.  So I've brought you a mirror. Look at yourself and remember me.
